on-freezable-extra-small"></i>Uncooked, if pastry not frozen</li></ul></div><div class="recipe-header__nutrition"><h3 class="recipe-header__nutrition-title"><strong>Nutrition:</strong> nutrition per serving (for 6)</h3><ul class="nutrition" itemprop="nutrition" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/NutritionInformation"><li><span class="nutrition__label">kcal</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="calories">522</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">fat</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="fatContent">24g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">saturates</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="saturatedFatContent">11g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">carbs</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="carbohydrateContent">76g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">sugars</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="sugarContent">6g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">fibre</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="fiberContent">6g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label">protein</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="proteinContent">5g</span></li><li><span class="nutrition__label nutrition__label--low">salt</span><span class="nutrition__value" itemprop="sodiumContent">0.36g</span></li></ul></div></div></div> </section><div class="recipe-header__actions"><div class="flyout"><a href="/user/login" class="btn btn--primary btn--save btn--block btn--icon-right" rel="nofollow"><span class="btn__text">Save <span class="wide-only">to My Good Food</span></span></a><div class="flyout__content"><div class="flyout__content-inner">Please <a href="/user/login?destination=node/102765">sign in</a> or <a href="/user/register?destination=node/102765">register</a> to save recipes.</div></div></div><div class="recipe-header__print"> <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="btn btn--default btn--icon-right btn--print"> <span class="btn__text">Print</span> <i class="font-icon font-icon-print"></i> </a></div></div></div> </header><div class="grid-padding"><div class="col span8"><div id="ad-mpu-premium-1-narrow" class="ad-mpu-premium-1-narrow"><div class="ad ad--mpu-premium-1-narrow" id="ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-db80b19efa"><script type="text/javascript">Drupal.GPT.createSlot("ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-db80b19efa", function () {var m = Drupal.GPT.buildSizeMapping([[[0,0],[[300,250]]],[[480,0],[[300,250],[300,600]]],[[770,0],[]]]);var s = googletag.defineSlot(Drupal.GPT.unitPath(), m.define, "ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-db80b19efa").defineSizeMapping(m.mapping.build()).setTargeting("pos", ["mpu_premium_1"]).addService(googletag.pubads());});</script></div></div><div id="recipetools" class="constantco-widget section-recipetools" data-app-resource-id="102765" data-type="recipetools" data-params="mobile_breakpoint=821"></div><div id="responsive-tabs" class="responsive-tabs responsive-tabs--2"><ul class="responsive-tabs__tabs"><li class="responsive-tabs__tab is-active"> <a href="#recipe-ingredients">Ingredients</a></li><li class="responsive-tabs__tab"> <a href="#recipe-method">Method</a></li></ul><div class="responsive-tabs__panes"> <section id="recipe-ingredients" class="responsive-tabs__pane is-active"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Ingredients</h2><div class="ingredients-list"><div class="ingredients-list__content"><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1½ kg apple(Braeburns or Granny Smiths are ideal)">1½ kg <a href="/glossary/apple" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">apple</a> (Braeburns or Granny Smiths are ideal)<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-259976" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/apple"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/apples.jpg?itok=lwz25SD0" width="100" height="100" alt="Apples" title="There are over 7,000 varieties of apple in existence, many of which are grown in Britain" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/apple">Apple</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ap-pel</span><p>Grown in temperate regions, apples are one of the most widely cultivated tree fruits. There are…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="squeeze lemon juice">squeeze lemon juice</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 cardamom podsor pinch of ground">2 cardamom pods or pinch of ground</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tbsp flour, plus extra for rolling">2 tbsp <a href="/glossary/flour" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">flour</a>, plus extra for rolling<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-257912" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/flour"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/flour_0.jpg?itok=f_OiRpqB" width="100" height="100" alt="Flour" title="Flour is a powdery ingredient usually made from grinding wheat, maize, rye, barley or rice" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/flour">Flour</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">fl-ow-er</span><p>Flour is a powdery ingredient usually made from grinding wheat, maize, rye, barley or rice. As…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="25g golden caster sugar, plus extra for sprinkling">25g golden caster sugar, plus extra for sprinkling</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="500g pack shortcrust pastry">500g pack shortcrust pastry</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tbsp milk">2 tbsp <a href="/glossary/milk" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">milk</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-260691" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/milk"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/milk-resized.jpg?itok=z-tC0wLi" width="100" height="100" alt="" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/milk">Milk</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">mill-k</span><p>One of the most widely used ingredients, milk is often referred to as a complete food. While cow…</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat oven to 220C/fan 200C/gas 7. Peel, core and quarter the apples, then cut into 1cm slices. Toss together with the lemon juice, then dab dry with kitchen paper so that the pie isn’t too watery. If you are using whole cardamom pods, split open the shell, remove the seed from inside and grind using a pestle and mortar. Mix into the apples with the flour and sugar, then toss to get everything coated.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Cut away a third of the pastry to divide into two pieces. Dust a little flour over a work surface, then roll out the larger piece to roughly 28cm wide and as thick as a £1 coin. Lift the pastry up (try loosely wrapping around a rolling pin) and spread over the bottom of a 22cm pie dish. Roll out the smaller piece of pastry a little larger than the top of the pie.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Pile up the apples inside and paint around the rim of the pie with milk. Lift the smaller circle of pastry on top. Press down to seal the pie, then trim around the edge of the pie with a sharp knife and discard the excess pastry. Use your fingers to indent around the pie and form a crimped edge.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Make a few slits in the pastry so that steam can escape, then brush all over with milk and sprinkle with extra sugar. Bake for 20 mins, then reduce oven to 190C/fan 170C/gas 5 and cook for 50 mins-1hr until the pastry is golden and crisp. If it starts to darken too much, cover with tin foil, but make sure you cook it uncovered for the final 10 mins so that the pastry can crisp. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, ice cream or custard.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1125529200" class="text-style-alt">September 2005</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-bo